utton inside the modal and nothing is posted back to the controller no account is deactivated/activated. If I set a break point on the controller action below and click publish, nothing happens. The breakpoint isnt hit.</p>  <pre><code>    public ActionResult ProviderActivate(FormCollection form) //change id to form post hidden element refer to TSProps     {         if (!CustomSecurity.IsAdmin(User.Identity.Name))             return RedirectToAction("Index", "Home");          string pid = form["pid"];          bool any = _db.CareProviders.Where(c =&gt; c.ProviderId == pid &amp;&amp; !c.Activated.HasValue).Any();         ....etc </code></pre>